```

BTW, is this the best way to determine a release build?

@aokolnychyi , thanks for sharing the progress!
I did not make myself clear. Yes, we could change the sort order for partitions. But regarding the individual sort order in the list of sort order in the metadata, is it allowed to change one of them? Say we have a sort order with id =1, sorting on source_column_id = 1 with ascending order, is it supported that it is updated to descending order? Shall we prohibit such kind of change, as it could run into problem when an existing data file is tied it, right? The data file is written with ascending order, but sort order id 1 it tied with says that it is the descending order.
Shall we only add new sort orders but could not change any existing ones?
